I. 3 Let the instantaneous speed of the magnet be $v$. Obtain the magnitude of the induced emf $\left(e_i\right)$ in the ring.

solution:
 Because of the relative speed $v$ between the magnet and the ring, in the field $\vec{B}=B_z \hat{k}+B_\rho \hat{\rho}$ of the magnet, the induced emf is given by
$$
\begin{aligned}
e_i & =\int(\vec{v} \times \vec{B}) \cdot d \vec{l} \\
e_i & =v B_a 2 \pi a
\end{aligned}
$$ where
$$
B_a=\frac{\mu_0}{4 \pi} \frac{3 p a\left(z_0-z\right)}{\left[a^2+\left(z_0-z\right)^2\right]^{5 / 2}}
$$

